ZCZC OE77
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 192300 UTC
A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE IS EXP OVER THE N SEA LATE SUNDAY ALTHOUGH THIS
WILL DECLINE EWARDS AS A LARGE AND COMPLEX AREA OF LOW PRESSURE DOMINATES
THE N ATLANTIC CENTRED TO THE SW OF ICELAND. THIS LOW IS EXP TO FILL EARLY
NXT WEEK BUT WITH SWARD TROUGH EXTENSION LEAVING SEVERAL SHALLOW LOW CENTRES
W OF IRELAND LATER MONDAY WHILE THE HIGH INTENSIFIES ONCE MORE OVER EERN
EUROPE. BY MID-WEEK THIS HIGH PRESSURE AREA REMAINS IN PLACE WHILE THE
LOW PRESSURE DEEPENS AND EXTENDS SWARDS TO FITZROY BY TUESDAY WITH CENTRAL
PRESSURE 990. THEN ON WEDNESDAY THE LOW CENTRE WILL EXTEND A TROUGH ACROSS
THE UK. STRG WINDS OR NEAR GALES DURING SUNDAY EVENING WILL MOD IN THE S
DURING MONDAY MORNING BUT CONTINUE STRG TO NEAR GALE AT TIMES IN THE N.
OCCASIONAL GALES ARE POSS IN FAIR ISLE FAEROES AND SE ICELAND LATER MONDAY
TUESDAY AND WEDNESDAY
